<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENAP70A7216023" svcinfotypenbr = "08" svcinfoqualnbr = "03" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "0">
<title>
A/C Refrigerant Pressure Sensor and Its Circuit Inspection
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENAP70A7216024">A/C Refrigerant Pressure Sensor Removal and Installation:Manual Type</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect A/C refrigerant pressure sensor connector.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Set ignition “ON”.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Check that voltage between “GRY/RED” wire terminal and “BLU/RED” wire terminal of A/C refrigerant pressure sensor connector is 4.75 V to 5.25 V.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If check result is not as specified, check A/C refrigerant pressure sensor circuit.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Connect A/C refrigerant pressure sensor connector with ignition “OFF”.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Connect manifold gauge set to charging valves.
</ptxt>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L7B103">
<s-part>
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09990-06020">
09990–06020
</s-number>
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Check A/C refrigerant pressure sensor voltage of ECM connector. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70A1104070"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If voltage is not as specified, replace A/C refrigerant pressure sensor.
</ptxt>
</s1>
